This [is the PDF at issue](https://www.docketalarm.com/cases/New_Jersey_Bankruptcy_Court/2--16-bk-20392/VeraAnn_Castellano/docs/1.pdf) that causes the problem. I fixed this bug by monkeypatching the function `_add_annots` in `pdfquery.py`:

```
    def _add_annots(self, layout, annots):
        """Adds annotations to the layout object
        """
        if annots:
            for annot in resolve1(annots):
                annot = resolve1(annot)
                if annot.get('Rect') is not None:
                    annot['bbox'] = annot.pop('Rect')  # Rename key
                    annot = self._set_hwxy_attrs(annot)
                try:
                    annot['URI'] = resolve1(annot['A'])['URI']
                except KeyError:
                    pass
                rep_keys = {}
                for k, v in six.iteritems(annot):
                    if not isinstance(v, six.string_types):
                        if ":" in k:
                            import logging
                            logging.warning("Converting key: %s"%k)
                            rep_keys[k] = k.replace(":", "_")
                        annot[k] = obj_to_string(v)
                for keyfrom, keyto in rep_keys.items():
                    annot[keyto] = annot[keyfrom]
                    del annot[keyfrom]
                elem = parser.makeelement('Annot', annot)
                layout.add(elem)
        return layout
````

Most of the code won't work with this forked version of tablesorter, but most of it would only require a simple change (for the pager Addon, not the widget).

## addPageList

In your version, it doesn't include filtered rows (using the filtered widget):

```js
function addPageList(table) {
  var i, len,
    c = table.config,
    p = c.pager;
  p.filteredRows = 0;
  normalized = c.cache[ 0 ].normalized;
  len = normalized.length;
  for ( i = 0; i < len; i++ ) {
    p.filteredRows += p.regexRows.test( normalized[ indx ][ c.columns ].$row[ 0 ].className ) ? 0 : 1;
  }
  p.filteredPages = Math.ceil( p.filteredRows / p.size );
  p.totalPages = Math.ceil(p.totalRows / p.size);
  c.container.find('ul').empty();
  for (i = 1; i <= c.filteredPages; i++) {
    c.container.find('ul').append('<li>' + i + '</li>');
  }
}
```

## setPage

In my forked version, you have access to these methods:

```js
$('table').trigger( method, [ value(s) ] );
```

* `pageAndSize` - See http://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/#pageandsize
* `pageSet` - See http://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/#pageset
* `pageSize` - See http://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/#pagesize

## addClass

In my forked version, use `table.config.pager` instead of `table.config`

```js
function addClass(table){
    var p = table.config.pager;
    p.$goto.children().removeClass('active');
    p.$container.find('li').eq(p.page).addClass('active');
}
```

## click Event

```js
table.config.pager.$goto.on( 'click', 'li', function() {
  var pageNum = parseInt( $(this).html(), 10 ) - 1;
  $(table).trigger('pageSet', pageNum);
  return false;
});
```

