@Garito thanks for separating the topics.

- **is_authenticated**: indeed, its name suggests that a `bool` should be returned, perhaps the evolution of the lib itself made this error prone for usage and understanding. We'll work on that.
- **pattern**: as I stated, we're moving towards a more flexible API if one needs to customize - but some messages in `authenticate` can be provided by you directly as it is today. If (these messages) are provided in any other protected method, then we should also work further to make this, at least, usable for everyone (given the effort one wants to spend extending / specializing a [method|object]). We just can't assume everyone will be pleased by any particular pattern, but we need to justify its usage and improve the code (where needed). There is some polishing in the way (as we plan more features), but our intention is always to be developer friendly, not otherwise. For now this may not pleases you, but we're trying to find time here and there to increment this library precisely on other developers needs (not only ours), so stay tuned, there are work to be done :wink:

